      "title": "Incremental changes described here",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Workflow 0: Baseline (No Isolation)\n\n### What This Shows\n\n**Top section:** A standard z-image-turbo pipeline. Every node runs in the ComfyUI host process with direct Python object passing.\n\n**Bottom section:** The same nodes recreated as `_Isolated` suffix nodes from IsolationToolKit. In this baseline, **none are connected** — they exist to show what’s available.\n\n### What Crosses the Process Boundary\n\n**Nothing.** This is the “before” state. All generation happens in the host process.\n\n### Series Progression\n\n| # | Workflow | What’s Added |\n|:--|:--|:--|\n| **0** | **No Isolation** | **Baseline — nothing connected** |\n| 1 | String Concatenation | STRING data crosses boundary |\n| 2 | Conditioning + Latent | CONDITIONING and LATENT tensors cross |\n| 3 | CLIP + VAE Objects | CLIP/VAE proxy objects cross |\n| 4 | ModelSampler | ModelSampling proxy crosses |\n| 5 | ModelPatcher | ModelPatcher proxy — full isolated sampling |\n| 6 | End to End | Complete isolated pipeline |\n| 7 | Shared Model | Zero-copy sharing back to host |\n\nEach workflow connects one more isolated node type, demonstrating incremental proxy complexity from simple data to zero-copy GPU tensors.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
    {
      "id": 84,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
