      "title": "Code from custom node",
      "properties": {},
      "widgets_values": [
        "## Code: The Isolated Node Pattern\n\n### Custom Node (`nodes/nodes_z_image_turbo.py`)\n\nEach `_ZIMG` node is a ComfyUI V3 API node:\n\n```python\nclass UNETLoader_ZIMG(io.ComfyNode):\n    @classmethod\n    def define_schema(cls):\n        return io.Schema(\n            node_id=\"UNETLoader_ZIMG\",\n            display_name=\"UNETLoader_Isolated\",\n            category=\"advanced/loaders\",\n            inputs=[...],\n            outputs=[io.Model.Output()],\n        )\n\n    @classmethod\n    def execute(cls, unet_name, weight_dtype):\n        model = comfy.sd.load_diffusion_model(...)\n        return io.NodeOutput(model)\n```\n\nThe code is identical to ComfyUI core nodes. The isolation is transparent to the node author.\n\n### Isolation Manifest (`pyproject.toml`)\n\n```toml\n[tool.comfy.isolation]\ncan_isolate = true\nshare_torch = true\n```\n\n### How It Works\n\nWhen `--use-process-isolation` is passed, `comfy/isolation/extension_loader.py` discovers this manifest and spawns a child process with its own venv. The child loads these V3 nodes in its own Python interpreter.\n\nWithout the flag, nodes run in-process like any other custom node.\n\n### Key Files\n\n- `nodes/nodes_z_image_turbo.py` — node implementations\n- `nodes/nodes_string.py` — string operations\n- `pyproject.toml` — isolation manifest\n- `comfy/isolation/extension_loader.py` — manifest discovery\n- `comfy/isolation/adapter.py` — type serialization\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#000"
    },
